PDZ domain, activate DegS cleavage of RseA, and induce sigma(E)-dependent 
transcription. These results suggest that DegS acts as a sensor of envelope 
stress by binding unassembled OMPs. DegS activation involves relief of 
inhibitory interactions between its PDZ and protease domains. Peptide binding to 
inhibitory PDZ domains in proteases related to DegS, including DegP/HtrA, may 
also regulate the degradation of specific substrates by these enzymes.

