the overall DNA binding properties of PhoP, structural superposition of the PhoP 
C-domain on the Escherichia coli PhoB C-domain-DNA complex suggests a 
base-specific interaction between Glu215 of PhoP and the ninth base of the DR1 
repeat motif. Biochemical experiments corroborate these results, showing that 
DNA recognition specificity can be altered by as little as a single residue 
