degradation, one Tn5 mutant which was able to grow with xanthine as a sole 
nitrogen source only in the presence of high molybdate concentrations (1 mM), a 
phenotype resembling Escherichia coli mogA mutants, was identified. 
Unexpectedly, the corresponding Tn5 insertion was located within the moeA gene. 
