growth sensitivity of the strains to oxygen, and they all exhibited clear 
compensatory up-expression of oxidative stress resistance proteins enabling 
survival of the bacterium. The most frequent up-expressed oxidative stress 
resistance factor (observed in 16 of the mutants) was the iron-sequestering 
protein NapA, linking iron sequestration with oxidative stress resistance. The 
up-expression of individual proteins in mutants ranged from 2 to 10 fold that of 
the wild type strain, even when incubated in a low O(2) environment. For 
