evolutionary relationship between alpha and gamma-family of PLP-dependent 
enzymes. The structure of the beta, beta, beta-trifluoroalanine inactivated CBL 
has been refined at 2.3 A resolution to an R-factor of 16.2%. It suggests that 
Lys210, the PLP-binding residue, mediates the proton transfer between C alpha 
and S gamma.

