protein-conducting channel in the cytoplasmic membrane of bacteria and the 
endoplasmic reticulum membrane of eukaryotes. It is engaged in both 
translocating secretory proteins across the membrane as well as in integrating 
membrane proteins into the lipid phase of the membrane. In the current study we 
have detected distinct SecYEG translocon complexes in native Escherichia coli 
membranes. Blue-Native-PAGE revealed the presence of a 200-kDa SecYEG complex in 
resting membranes. When the SecA-dependent secretory protein pOmpA was trapped 
inside the SecYEG channel, a smaller SecY-containing complex of approximately 
140-kDa was observed, which probably corresponds to a monomeric SecYEG-substrate 
