in the SecYEG translocon, resulted in two complexes of 250 and 600 kDa, each 
containing both SecY and the translocon-associated membrane protein YidC. The 
appearance of both complexes was correlated with the number of transmembrane 
domains that were exposed during targeting of mannitol permease to the membrane. 
