and SecA/SecB-mediated translocation do not only represent two independent 
protein delivery systems, but also remain mechanistically distinct processes 
even at the level of the membrane where they engage different domains of SecY 
and different components of the translocon. In addition, the experimental setup 
used here enabled us to demonstrate that SRP-dependent integration of a 
multispanning protein into membrane vesicles leads to a biologically active 
enzyme.

