Most membrane proteins are co-translationally inserted into the lipid bilayer 
via the universally conserved SecY complex and they access the lipid phase 
presumably via a lateral gate in SecY. In bacteria, the lipid transfer of 
membrane proteins from the SecY channel is assisted by the SecY-associated 
protein YidC, but details on the SecY-YidC interaction are unknown. By employing 
an in vivo and in vitro site-directed cross-linking approach, we have mapped the 
SecY-YidC interface and found YidC in contact with all four transmembrane 
