which recruits a ribosome, activating translation. Using NMR spectroscopy, we 
show that only a complete ops-paused transcription elongation complex activates 
RfaH, probably via a transient encounter complex, allowing the refolded CTD to 
bind ribosomal protein S10. We also demonstrate that upon release from the 
elongation complex, the CTD transforms back into the autoinhibitory α-state, 
resetting the cycle. Transformation-coupled autoinhibition allows RfaH to 
achieve high specificity and potent activation of gene expression.

