structure, flipping out a conserved T residue that is specifically recognized by 
RfaH. Molecular modeling and genetic evidence support the notion that ops 
hairpin is required for RfaH recruitment. We argue that both the sequence and 
the structure of the non-template strand are read out by transcription factors, 
expanding the repertoire of transcriptional regulators in all domains of life.

