KdpDE-mediated signal transduction. Moreover, the DBD-CA interface largely 
overlapped with that of the DBD-DNA complex, leading to competition between KdpD 
and its target promoter in a KdpE phosphorylation-dependent manner. In addition, 
the extended C-terminal tail of the CA domain was critical for stabilizing the 
interaction with KdpDE and for signal transduction. Together, these data provide 
a molecular basis for specific KdpD and KdpE interactions that play key roles in 
efficient signal transduction and transcriptional regulation by this TCS.

