spread these microorganisms. The aim of this study was to investigate the 
intestinal carriage of these bacteria in Syrian refugees in Lebanon. Between 
June and July 2019, 250 rectal swabs were collected from two refugee camps in 
North Lebanon. Swabs were cultured on different selective media. Antibiotic 
susceptibility testing was performed using the disk diffusion method. 
