sensor-response regulator two-component systems that convert a specific input 
into a distinct output pattern. Cross talk, the unwanted transfer of signals 
between circuits, occurs when a response regulator is phosphorylated 
inappropriately from a noncognate source. Cross talk is inhibited in part by the 
high interaction specificity between cognate sensor-response regulator pairs. 
