anaerobic activation of the operon. Rather, anaerobic activation of the operon 
was largely dependent on the global regulator ArcA and a GTPase MnmE. Under 
aerobic condition, transcription of gadE was repressed by the global DNA 
silencer H-NS in M9 minimal medium. Interestingly, under anaerobic condition, 
while ΔarcA almost completely abolished transcription of gadE-mdtEF, further 
deletion of hns in ΔarcA mutant restored the transcription of the full-length 
PgadE-lacZ, and P1- and P3-lacZ fusions, suggesting an antagonistic effect of 
