of LEE- and non-LEE-encoded effectors and the upregulation of genes for 
glutamate-dependent acid resistance (GDAR). Upregulation of GDAR genes 
corresponded with a marked increase in acid resistance. GrvA-dependent 
regulation of GDAR and the LEE required gadE, the central activator of GDAR 
genes and a direct repressor of the LEE. Control of gadE by GrvA was further 
determined to occur through downregulation of the gadE activator GadW. This 
interaction of GrvA with GadW-GadE represses the acid resistance phenotype, 
