apparatus, encoded on the LEE pathogenicity island. This study investigates the 
mechanism whereby the DNA-binding regulator GrvA coordinates activation of the 
LEE with repression of GDAR. Investigating how these systems are regulated leads 
to an understanding of pathogenic behavior and novel strategies aimed at disease 
prevention and control.

