Bacterial signal transduction systems can be viewed as an entity of 
multi-sensory and output domains, whereas the functions of response regulators 
play a pivotal role in the complex network interactions. One crucial property 
among response regulators functions is their oligomerization and subsequent 
binding to DNA. The AtoS-AtoC two component system, functionally modulated by 
various agents, influences fundamental cellular processes such as short-chain 
fatty acid catabolism and poly-(R)-3-hydroxybutyrate biosynthesis in Escherichia 
