reductase (NorVW)); cellular responses under oxidative and nitrosative stress 
conditions were assessed. Spectroscopic changes of the Cgb and Ctb haems in 
soluble fractions after oxidation by NO were evaluated. Construction of E. coli 
nor mutants and a ubiquinone-defective strain allowed the exploration of the 
flavorubredoxin reductase and the aerobic respiratory chain as candidates for 
Cgb electron donors in E. coli mutants.
