QseB/QseC is a two-component system that is involved in the regulation of 
multiple bacterial behaviors by regulating quorum sensing, bacterial 
pathogenicity, and antibiotic resistance. Thus, QseB/QseC could provide a target 
for new antibiotic development. Recently, QseB/QseC has been found to confer 
survival advantages to environmental bacteria under stress conditions. The 
molecular mechanistic understanding of QseB/QseC has become an active area of 
