to inhaled LPS in normal subjects is a prerequisite to define the safety 
threshold of exposure. In the present study, the clinical and inflammatory 
responses to rising doses of inhaled LPS was evaluated. Nine normal volunteers 
were challenged weekly by inhalation with saline, 0.5, 5, and 50 microg LPS 
