multiple uhp genes were generated by use of restriction sites at the ends of the 
Km cassette. The phenotypes of the Km insertions and the in-frame deletions 
confirmed that all three regulatory genes are required for Uhp function. Whereas 
the deletion of uhpA completely abolished the expression of a uhpT-lacZ reporter 
gene, the deletion of uhpB or uhpC resulted in a partially elevated basal level 
of expression that was not further inducible. These results indicated that UhpB 
and perhaps UhpC play both positive and negative roles in the control of uhpT 
