mutations: R282V in galU (M7 from M3); Q558∗ in lon (M8 from M4). Introduction 
of uhpB or uhpC mutations by site-directed mutagenesis conferred a 128-fold 
increase in fosfomycin MICs, whereas single mutations in galU or lon were only 
responsible for a 2-fold increase. Also, these mutations abolished the induction 
