accumulation of the glmS transcript in a GlmZ-dependent manner. Concomitantly, 
GlmZ accumulates in its unprocessed form. Hence, we conclude that the biological 
function of GlmZ is to positively control the glmS mRNA in response to GlcN-6-P 
concentrations and that YhbJ negatively regulates GlmZ. As in yhbJ mutants 
