recognize the groE promoter. These observations altogether indicate that strict 
difference exists in the promoter selectivity between two molecular species of 
the RNA polymerase holoenzyme. The groE transcription in vitro was not affected 
significantly within the temperature range from 32 to 42 degrees C. The two 
sigma subunits could be replaced in vitro on the same core enzyme, supporting 
the view that the spectrum of gene expression in E. coli is under a dynamic 
control by intracellular levels of individual sigma subunits.

