operons encoding ribosomal proteins, and the majority upstream and proximal 
ribosome binding sites, suggesting a regulatory role of processing on 
translation initiation. The processed transcripts showed increased stability and 
translation efficiency. Particularly, processing within the tricistronic 
transcript of rplA-rplJ-rplL enhanced the translation of rplL, which can provide 
a driving force for the 1:4 stoichiometry of L10 to L12 in the ribosome. 
