A new genetic screening method has been developed to isolate Escherichia coli 
promoters which are components of the SOS regulon. Plasmids containing the 
regulatory regions of polB (dinA) and two new loci, dinG and dinH, were 
characterized. Galactokinase gene fusion experiments indicated that 
transcription of these genes is inducible by treatment with mitomycin and 
conforms to a classical model of SOS regulation involving simple LexA 
repression. Mapping studies using the E. coli DNA library of Kohara et al. (Y. 
