dinH are located at 17.8 and 19.8 min on the chromosome, respectively. The 
nucleotide sequence of the dinH regulatory region contains a segment which is 
very similar to previously characterized binding sites for LexA protein. An 
asymmetric, noncanonical 20-bp LexA operator in the cloned dinG promoter region 
