sequence of the gene immediately downstream of the DNA damage-inducible polB 
locus encodes a polypeptide which has extensive sequence homology to several 
known and putative DNA and RNA helicase proteins. This gene, which is not 
regulated by the LexA repressor, has been designated hepA. The predicted amino 
acid sequence of the product of hepA contains several highly conserved sequence 
motifs that are also found in enzymes such as the RecQ and UvrB proteins of E. 
coli and the Rad3 protein of Saccharomyces cerevisiae.

