FumA and FumB during growth with vanillin. Surprisingly, vanillin-dependent 
reduction pf copper (II) to copper (I) led to upregulation of the copA gene and 
growth in the presence of vanillin was shown to be hypersensitive to inhibition 
by copper ions. AcrD and AaeAB were identified as potential vanillin efflux 
systems. Vanillin-tolerant strains isolated by ALE had distinct nonsynonymous 
