The ferric citrate transport system of Escherichia coli is the first example of 
a transcription initiation mechanism that starts at the cell surface. The 
inducer, ferric citrate, binds to an outer membrane transport protein, and 
without further transport elicits a signal that is transmitted across the outer 
membrane, the periplasm, and the cytoplasmic membrane into the cytoplasm. Signal 
